main event: Multiple unidentified objects were reported in the sky on October 6, 1956, by observers from the Combr Air Division Defense.
interesting points: Four unidentified objects were reported by observers Wilkins, Wilkes, and Rjebu., The objects were described as elliptical-shaped fireballs with smoke trails., Sighting lasted 3-5 seconds with an estimated speed of 700-4500 mph., No sound was heard during the observation., The weather was clear at the time of the sighting.
witness description: Observers from the Combr Air Division Defense.
